raw_data.title: Senior Program Manager
raw_data.description: The Senior Program Manager is the Principal of the company with a high school diploma and minimum of 10 years plus experience in management. The Senior Program Manager has the ability to make business decisions, authority to contract labor, add/reduce crew size, secure necessary equipment and supplies, while maintaining relationships with suppliers and end?users on a continual basis. Strong knowledge of GSA Contracts.

raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: The Project Manager must have a high school diploma with a minimum of five years’ experience in the industry or related fields. They will be responsible for coordinating deliveries, installation of product, setting up installation schedules for products, and punch list. They must have working knowledge of all material suppliers and GSA Schedule Terms and Conditions. In addition, they will perform safety meetings and supervise safe working conditions per OSHA guidelines.

raw_data.title: Foreman Installer
raw_data.description: The Foreman Installer must have a minimum high school diploma, with ten plus years’ experience in the related field of work. Their past experience must include working with a formidable installation company or related industry. They must have complete knowledge of every product line and the warranted installation procedure for each. We expect them to participate in manufacturer installation training, including product specifications, electrical, construction, packaging, and maintenance. They must have the ability to read and understand CAD drawings, blueprints, bill of materials, acknowledgements and receiving reports. In addition, they will perform safety meetings and supervise safe working conditions per OSHA guidelines

raw_data.title: Lead Installer

raw_data.title: Skilled Installer
raw_data.description: The skilled Installer must have a minimum high school diploma or greater. Minimum 3 years’ experience with furniture installation or a related field is preferred. This person must have a clear background and security records for proper base access. They must have experience in an assembly, construction or mechanical field including handling equipment, power tools, and cutting blades. They must be able to accurately measure, align parts, and follow installation instructions, with the ability to lift heavy boxes, load, and off load trucks.

raw_data.title: Movers/Installers

This person must have a clear background and security records for proper base access. They must have experience in an assembly, construction or mechanical field including handling equipment, power tools, and cutting blades. They must be able to accurately measure, align parts, and follow installation instructions, with the ability to lift heavy boxes, load, and off load trucks.

raw_data.title: FF&E Interior Designer
raw_data.description: FF&E Interior Designer, must have a minimum high school diploma with 10 years field experience collaborating directly with a designer, including on hand knowledge acquired for the scope of work performed. They will be responsible for accuracy of CAD layouts, systems integration, design boards, finish selection, specifying entire scopes of work, and solutions to the miscellaneous items. This includes working knowledge of all material suppliers and GSA Schedule Terms and Conditions.

raw_data.title: Warehouse Supervisor
raw_data.description: The Warehouse Supervisor must have a minimum high school diploma or greater, with five years’ experience in the related field of work. They must be able to physically maneuver equipment, lift cartons, direct other warehouse employees, have experience with fork?lift operation, and other material handling equipment. They must have a good understanding of storage techniques and warehouse management. In addition, they will perform safety meetings and supervise safe working conditions per OSHA guidelines.

raw_data.title: Warehouse Laborer
raw_data.description: The Warehouse Laborer must have a minimum high school diploma or equivalent. They must have two years’ experience in storage, retail/ commercial warehousing, or a related field. They will have the physical ability to move products, haul pallets, stack, offload trucks, stage for transport, and load trucks for delivery to a jobsite.
